headline: Goldman Sachs downgrades General Mills, Conagra on cost pressures, weak demand
summary: Investing.com -- Goldman Sachs downgraded shares of General Mills (NYSE:GIS) and Conagra Brands (NYSE:CAG), citing ongoing cost pressures and sluggish demand for packaged food products, while maintaining its Sell rating on Kraft Heinz (NASDAQ:KHC).

headline: High Liner to buy Mrs. Paul’s, Van de Kamp’s seafood brands from Conagra
summary: Paul Jewer, High Liner’s president and CEO, called the deal “highly strategic”, adding it will act as a “catalyst for further growth in the US retail market”.
